\fs55\fsmilli27648 \cf2 \cb3 A lollapalooza effect occurs when several network models are combined and implemented to produce a desired result. The often synergistic results of this combined impact can be quite dramatic.\cb1 \
\cb3 For example, in order to combat the HIV virus, a three-drug \'93cocktail\'94 was developed. While the individual drugs weren\'92t effective, the combination of several medications was extremely successful. Another example of a lollapalooza effect can be seen in open-outcry auctions. These auctions involve buyers and sellers grouped together around an auctioneer who initiates the bidding process. The participants then attempt to outbid one other to win the item being auctioned. Charlie Munger summed up the effects in this way:\cb1 \
