\cb3 NOTE: Virtually all of the aforementioned effects apply to the stock market when investments are made during both bull and bear periods. Superior results can be found in industries where destructive pricing behavior is absent. A company in an industry with this characteristic might well have above average financial results. If the company were also in an industry that is riding a long-term wave (surfing), then its results could grow for a substantial length of time. The more of these factors that are present, the more likely the company is worth watching as a potential future investment.}